snippet.textDisplay: Funny how the reviewers keep trying to compare the corvette to cars costing 3 and 4x the base cost of the vette when this isn’t the market GM is going for much less cares to go after.   Although with a few mods and some engine tweaking this car will easily hold its own with any Lambo or Mcclaren.  We also need to remember this is the first generation of the new  platform, so I’m sure there will be a supercar deflator in the gen 8’s future.  From a reliability and cost of maintenance standpoint the exotics will cost many time more to keep and spend many more trips on the back of a flat bed than even the most problematic corvette will ever torture it’s owner with.

snippet.textDisplay: This is such a Ferrari wanna-be.  No Corvette should have a mid-engine.  The Corvette, by its very nature, is front-engine rear wheel drive.  6,500 rpm red line?  My Nissan Frontier has a 6,250 red line and my tachometer goes all the way to 8,000!  Just my opinion, and I know plenty of people disagree with me, but I personally think Chevrolet absolutely destroyed the Corvette name with this car.  It's disgusting for wearing the Corvette badge.  Ford screwed up as well with the Mustang Mach-E.  No Mustang should be electric.  What is happening to American vehicles anymore??
